textAnnotations.description:
MASHED POTATO-STUFFED FRANKS: Peel and
cook 4 medium-sized potatoes in salted water. Drain
and mash. Add 2 teaspoons grated onion, 4 teaspoon salt,
a dash of pepper, 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons
milk. Beat until light and fluffy. Make lengthwise
slits in 6 frankfurters and spread open. Fill slits
with the mashed potato. Top each with a teaspoon
of chili sauce. Broil 4" from heat about 5 minutes
or until lightly browned. Makes 6. For a
tasty variation, stir 4 cup finely shredded
American cheese into the hot mashed potato.
